 enchanters will make more and more apperances in  your groups, and at higher levels 40+, most folks will not go into a dungeon without one, reason being enchanters break up spawns, if you can't find a chanter, find a bard, ranger, druid, or monk, all have not as good as chanters, but ways of breaking up spawns. now scuse me but i didn't even come close to answering your question of how do mages help <br>
Well first off in group mages have one main job, We assist, we can do other things, our pet can tank, we can nuke, we can even heal (100 bind wounds right here Woot!) just very poorly, but mainly we make great assisters, so first off, whenever you get in group find out who is main tank, this guy is the person you will have targeted half the time second, have an assist button, put it on a hot key page, and have it be /assist thats all it has to be, and keep your tank targeted before he pulls, when he gets there hit your assist button and sic your pet ( i also believe your assist button can be /assist &lt;tank name&gt; but i'm not sure of this), then DS the tank with  your most recent damage shield (always keep your main tank DSed, IMO it does more damage than our biggest nukes at the levels mana wise, right now at 41 my DS works out to about 600 damage total for only 100mana) after this, you can either med, nuke the mob once, malise the mob, up to you, depending on how my mana is doing and how many other mobs we have to fight I may or may not nuke, but thats up to you to decide when you feel comfortable nuking, and when you think you need to med, now you will fight this way no matter if you have crowd control or not, if you have a chanter, he should throw AE mez and everything but the one you are all fightig should me mezzed and you drop the mobs one at a time, if you dont' have crowd control, you'll still fight the same way, cause your group should always all be on the same mob, so as an answer to your question, if you wanna help break up spawns, learn to ASSIST, <br>
btw some other notes on how to be great in group, If you wanna impress folks, and get your name circulating as a mage worth having around, there is one main thing you have got to learn, its not when to nuke (though this is good tolearn), its not to DS the tank (though this is also good to learn) the only thing that a group sees in a mage, is how well you control your pet, your pets your weapon, use him well, and the group will love ya, break a chanters mez with em more than once, and the group will hate you, get good with /pet calm down, or in even more dire circumstances /pet get lost (better to lose ones pet, then lose ones Cleric because he got agged on becuase he healed the chanter, who was getting his face beat in, cause the mob he was trying to mez keeps getting broke by your pet)<br>
also get good with your assist button, you can avoid most problems if you simply make sure your on the same thinking with your tank, also i'd suggest letting a fight start before siccing your pet, let the tank start the fight, let the chanter lay down some crowd control, and after you have made sure your siccing your pet on the same mob your tank is fighting, then send him, better late then at the wrong mob. Also some other suggestions, first off, when your puller grabs too many and your chanter is gonna have a tough time mezzing em all, good way to make a chanter buddy is to hold your pet back and assist em if he gets in trouble, /tell em before hand to let him now what your planning to do, but if the tank pulls 5, your chanter mezzes three and two rush him, sic your pet on one of em, then mash back off, this gives the chanter time to land his stun, you to get your pet out, and him to land mez, its risky at times, but with practice, you'll have a friend for life if Jabober saved your chanter from two mobs beating him into a lil pulp, <br>
Okay one other thing then i gotta go, while i'm on the subject of chanters, and other what not, i was lookig at my spell book the other day and i noticed my level 39 AE based around caster nuke Flame Arc, its 173 damage to all mobs around me for 179 mana, now there is only one problem with it, I have to run up between all of them and try to cast it, and so far my sucess rate at that is 0 to 372, its suicide cause mobs hate casters at highere levels and will let the tank beat on em, if it means hitting your soft skinned hide, BUT, the other day i was sitting there and i my groups tank pulled 3 mobs (we were in OT, it was a rhino, a sarnak, and a cacti for those of you taking notes)<br>
well the tank yelled rhino first, then knight, so he got up there turned around and started in on the Rhino, i tabbed assist, checked to make sure it read rhino, and sent Jabober in to kick some butt, the chanter mezzed the other two with AE mez, i renewed the DS on the Tank, the Druid healed the tank once, and we all medded, well after the rhino dropped , the tanks started in on the knight, well bout this time Mez broke and the cacti rushed our chanter, well i stood up to assist the tank, i noticed the chanter ran up to the tank so the knight, and cacti were next to each other, he then proceeded to stun lock the both of em , the knight dropped quickly, then they finished the cacti<br>
i sent the chanter a tell and asked him if he always stunned on two mobs to go ( btw it it tough finding a chanter who stuns, most chanters don't utilize all the abilites they have ) he answered no, go right ahead and my mage brain started turning, I asked him if he minded if i thru in an AE nuke the next time he stunned, he answered yes, so i summoned Flame Arc, and we told our tank to pull two, well he came up with a berzerker and a knight, the chanter ran down to stun so i ran down, and started casting as soon as his first stun hit,his second stun hit and then Baam! my AE nuke hit, 173 damage to both of the mobs for 179 mana, I just did around 350 damage for 180 mana, and had a spell graphic to boot, and i softened up the next mob for the tanks, now i'll explain why this works, first off the stun lets you cast, cause they can't swing for 10 seconds, easily enough time for you to get your nuke off, second, mobs gain less aggro while stunned, normally AE is a bad idea cause you risk agging all of them but if you can get em stunned, AE is great for the mana efficiency (and the kick ass spell graphics ) so find a good chanter, get him to trust you, and throw in those AE! anyway i've jabbed till i can't jab no more, hope this helps<br>
<br>
Annoden Fizzlemoor <br>
